The author reflects on their experience of knowing Alcee Hastings, a former member of the House of Representatives and a civil rights lawyer. They admired Hastings for his sense of humor, his honesty, and his dedication to fighting for equality. Despite growing up in the Jim Crow South, Hastings was passionate about helping America fulfill its promise to all citizens. Throughout his career, he fought for desegregation and advocated for the rights of working people. The author expresses sadness at Hastings' passing and sends their condolences to his family.